title: Keys and Rooms
content:
There are  rooms and you start in room 0.  Each room has a distinct number in , and each room may have some keys to access the next room. 
Formally, each room  has a list of keys , and each key  is an integer in  where .  A key  opens the room with number .
Initially, all the rooms start locked (except for room 0). 
You can walk back and forth between rooms freely.
Return  if and only if you can enter every room.
